COVID-19 applications are mobile software applications specifically designed to help track people who are in contact in response to the 2019-20 coronavirus pandemic, meaning the process of identifying people (“contacts”) who may have been in contact with an infected person.
Many applications have been designed or proposed with official government support in some regions and jurisdictions.
