A local IT association has designed the app, released it as an open-source app and is due to be handed over to the government. North Macedonia has launched StopKorona!, a Bluetooth-based app to track exposure to potentially infected individuals and provide rapid response to healthcare authorities.
The Ministry of Communications and Technology, in collaboration with the Ministry of Health, has taken over the design of the application.
